00:18:51.640 --> 00:18:54.720
Interesting thing about RCA
Victor, does anyone know the story

00:18:54.720 --> 00:18:56.460
about Carl Engel and bringing

00:18:56.460 --> 00:19:02.070
in Victor Talking recordings
back in the 20s?

00:19:02.070 --> 00:19:04.310 position:56%
Does anyone know who Carl Engel was?

00:19:04.310 --> 00:19:06.640 position:56%
No music division people can answer?

00:19:06.640 --> 00:19:10.280
So Carl Engel was the third
chief of the music division.

00:19:10.280 --> 00:19:15.180
He came into office in
1922 and lasted until 1934,

00:19:15.180 --> 00:19:18.680 position:56%
in which case he got a more powerful
job outside, I guess he saw it

00:19:18.680 --> 00:19:21.090
that way; he went to become
president of G. Schirmer.

00:19:21.090 --> 00:19:24.010
And when he came into the
music division he was all

00:19:24.010 --> 00:19:26.350
about growing the collections
and fulfilling the mission

00:19:26.350 --> 00:19:30.850
that Sonic had put in
place previous to him.

00:19:30.850 --> 00:19:36.300 position:56%
Engel developed a relationship with
the Victor Talking Record company --

00:19:36.300 --> 00:19:38.090
Victor Talking Machine company.

00:19:38.090 --> 00:19:42.360
And he kind of haggled them
for two years to get them

00:19:42.360 --> 00:19:46.150 position:56%
to donate recordings of commercial
releases and other unpublished stuff

00:19:46.150 --> 00:19:48.320
to the library to develop
a sound collection.

00:19:48.320 --> 00:19:51.250
And there was some wax cylinder
that existed somewhere before,

00:19:51.250 --> 00:19:55.580
but in the literature that I've
found it said that Engel's project

00:19:55.580 --> 00:19:58.270
with the Victor Company was really
the beginning of our sound archive

00:19:58.270 --> 00:19:59.720
in the sense that we know today.

00:19:59.720 --> 00:20:01.760
So over the course of
Engel's tenure they brought

00:20:01.760 --> 00:20:03.060
in a few thousand recordings.

00:20:03.060 --> 00:20:06.590
Some of those were selected
by Engel and his staff

00:20:06.590 --> 00:20:09.490
from the Victor catalogues.

00:20:09.490 --> 00:20:13.000
And later on, as the relationship
kind of weakened a bit,

00:20:13.000 --> 00:20:14.670
the Victor Company
was just sending stuff

00:20:14.670 --> 00:20:16.530
that they thought would
be worthwhile

00:20:16.530 --> 00:20:19.910
for the music division
sound collections.

00:20:19.910 --> 00:20:23.160
And nowadays there's a whole
recorded sound section as we know

00:20:23.160 --> 00:20:25.620
and they have over 3.5
million recordings.

00:20:25.620 --> 00:20:28.890 position:56%
So it's kind of cool that the former
chief of the music division had

00:20:28.890 --> 00:20:31.560
such an impact over time
starting from a little idea

00:20:31.560 --> 00:20:33.660
and pestering of a
commercial entity.

